|title=Reasons to be cheerful
|author=Tom Fordyce
|work=BBC Sport
|date=14 June 2004
|accessdate=29 August 2007}}&lt;/ref&gt; In 2004, following the death of [[Brian Clough]], Robson briefly stood in for Clough as a columnist at ''[[FourFourTwo]]'' magazine, and from 2004 onwards wrote a weekly column for ''[[The Mail on Sunday]]''.&lt;ref&gt;{{cite news
|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/pages/live/columnists/sportcolumnists.html?in_page_id=1951
